This paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a joint space learning method using an attribute-guided attention mechanism and a semantic consistent adversary strategy, which involves machine learning techniques such as adversarial learning and attention mechanisms. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also deals with cross-modality matching, which involves multimedia analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves semantic consistency, which is a topic in natural language processing and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with surveillance applications, which involves security and cryptography, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category.
